\i DMA
\i0  - Check this box if you want to enable the\
		bus master IDE controller to perform DMA transfers to and\
		from the hard drive. When enabled, the CPU is only\
		responsible for setting up the transfer. The controller then\
		proceed to perform DMA transfers between the hard drive\
		and the system memory. An interrupt is generated at the \
		end of the transfer to signal the CPU that the transfer is \
		complete. While the transfer is taking place, the CPU is not\
		burdened with the data transfer itself, and it is able \
		to perform other tasks. Disk throughput may improve\
		depending on the disk and the speed of the system.\
		\
9. 	Click Done, then click Save, then quit Configure.\

